dcterms:description: The Arcade Learning Environment (ALE) is a benchmark for evaluating reinforcement learning algorithms, providing a suite of Atari games for testing agent performance.
dcterms:title: Arcade Learning Environment (ALE)

dcterms:creator: M. G. Bellemare
Y. Naddaf
J. Veness
M. Bowling
dcterms:description: BREAKOUT is one of the Atari games included in the Arcade Learning Environment, used to evaluate the performance of reinforcement learning algorithms.
dcterms:title: BREAKOUT (Atari Game)

dcterms:creator: M. G. Bellemare
Y. Naddaf
J. Veness
M. Bowling
dcterms:description: SEAQUEST is another Atari game included in the Arcade Learning Environment, known for its complexity and used to assess the performance of reinforcement learning algorithms.
dcterms:title: SEAQUEST (Atari Game)

dcterms:creator: M. G. Bellemare
Y. Naddaf

M. Bowling
dcterms:description: ASTERIX is an Atari game included in the Arcade Learning Environment, used to demonstrate the effects of overestimation in reinforcement learning algorithms.
dcterms:title: ASTERIX (Atari Game)

dcterms:creator: J. Boyan

dcterms:description: Gridworld is a common reinforcement learning benchmark that allows for exact computation of the optimal value function, used to evaluate various reinforcement learning algorithms.
dcterms:title: Gridworld
